CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F378A1783961289
OL,3,CFootball fans clash with police after
OL,4,CMorocco knocked out of World Cup
OL,6,FThe Metropolitan Police said four
OL,7,Fpeople were arrested for violent
OL,8,Fdisorder and one officer had been
OL,9,Ftaken to hospital with a head injury
OL,10,Fafter being hit by a glass bottle.
OL,12,FThe force said:
OL,14,F"Officers were initially called after
OL,15,Fa group of people congregated in the
OL,16,Froad and blocked traffic.
OL,18,F"The incident then escalated with the
OL,19,Fgroup throwing bottles and setting off
OL,20,Ffireworks.
OL,26,@vD@AOUzD@AOU
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G2/5
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,379,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F378A1783961289
OL,3,CFootball fans clash with police after
OL,4,CMorocco knocked out of World Cup
OL,6,F"As a result, further officers were
OL,7,Fdeployed to the area.
OL,9,F"One officer was taken to hospital for
OL,10,Fhead injuries; it is believed he had
OL,11,Fbeen hit by a glass bottle.
OL,13,F"No other injuries were reported.
OL,14,FOfficers remained in the area and made
OL,15,Ffour arrests for violent disorder,
OL,16,Fwith the group dispersing and the road
OL,17,Freopened from around 1am.
OL,19,F"We will not tolerate such disorder on
OL,20,Four streets, or attacks on our
OL,21,Fofficers.
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@AOUuD@AOU{D@AOU
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G3/5
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,379,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F378A1783961289
OL,3,CFootball fans clash with police after
OL,4,CMorocco knocked out of World Cup
OL,6,F"A police presence will remain in the
OL,7,Farea overnight and we will be
OL,8,Freviewing CCTV and video footage
OL,9,Fcirculating on social media to ensure
OL,10,Fall those responsible are brought to
OL,11,Fjustice."
OL,13,FThe UK Football Policing Unit (UKFPU)
OL,14,Frecorded 223 incidents related to the
OL,15,FEngland-Mexico match in the early
OL,16,Fhours of Monday morning in England and
OL,17,FWales.
OL,19,FCouncillor Paul Swaddle, leader of
OL,20,FWestminster City Council, responded to
OL,21,Fthe incident. He said:
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@IO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G4/5
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,379,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F378A1783961289
OL,3,CFootball fans clash with police after
OL,4,CMorocco knocked out of World Cup
OL,6,F"I am deeply disturbed by scenes of
OL,7,Fcrowd disorder on the Edgware Road
OL,8,Fcirculating on social media after last
OL,9,Fnight's World Cup results.
OL,11,F"It is completely unacceptable that
OL,12,FMetropolitan police officers appear to
OL,13,Fhave been turned on by some groups and
OL,14,Fone officer injured as they were
OL,15,Freportedly pelted with bottles.
OL,17,F"I condemn this behaviour and appeal
OL,18,Fto all fans to be respectful
OL,19,Fthroughout the tournament."
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@AOUyD@AOU{D@[O]
